 One of the owners of an electronics shop gutted in a fire incident at Ikpoba Hill Market Benin in Ikpoba-Okha Local Government Area of Edo has collapsed. The owner identified as Tony was immediately rushed to a nearby hospital after he saw the level of destruction of his goods. Goods worth millions were lost to the inferno, which started around 9pm on Saturday. Over 15 shops were affected by the disaster. One of the witnesses, Peter, revealed men of Edo Fire Service that responded to the distress call watched helplessly as the fire raged on.